findings.fix:
Replace all occurrences of:
```ts
const identity = await ctx.auth.getUserIdentity();
if (identity === null) throw new Error('Not authenticated');
const userId = identity.subject;
```
With:
```ts
const { userId } = await requireAuth(ctx);
```
Add `import { requireAuth } from './lib/auth';`.

Pass the timestamp in as an argument from the client and validate it is within a reasonable range, or derive it from `ctx.scheduler` scheduling time. Example:
```ts
args: { ..., subscribedAt: v.number() }
// client passes Date.now() before calling the mutation
```

Accept the week start timestamp as an arg from the client (the client already knows what week it is):
```ts
export const currentWeekDigest = query({
  args: { weekStartTimestamp: v.number() },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const { userId } = await requireAuth(ctx);
    return ctx.db.query('weeklyDigest')
      .withIndex('by_userId_weekStart', q => q.eq('userId', userId).eq('weekStartTimestamp', args.weekStartTimestamp))
      .first();
  }
});
```

If `aiAnalysis` is null, fail explicitly rather than silently falling back to wall-clock time:
```ts
if (!aiAnalysis) {
  console.warn(`[updateFoodTrialSummary] aiAnalysis ${args.aiAnalysisId} not found, skipping`);
  return { updated: 0 };
}
const windowAnchor = aiAnalysis.timestamp;
```

Consider adding rate-limit metadata to the user's profile or a dedicated `rateLimits` table — check it at the start of the action and increment on success. A simple per-minute or per-hour counter would prevent runaway consumption:
```ts
// Pseudocode
const usage = await ctx.runQuery(internal.rateLimits.checkAndIncrement, { userId, window: '1h', limit: 50 });
if (!usage.allowed) throw new Error('[NON_RETRYABLE] [QUOTA_ERROR] Rate limit exceeded');
```

Replace `v.string()` with a `v.union(v.literal(...), ...)` allowlist of permitted model identifiers, or validate against a set at runtime:
```ts
const ALLOWED_MODELS = new Set(['gpt-4.1-nano', 'gpt-4o-mini', 'gpt-4o']);
if (!ALLOWED_MODELS.has(args.model)) throw new Error('[NON_RETRYABLE] [KEY_ERROR] Model not permitted');
```

Remove the inner conditional when `deleteOrphans` is true — just delete unconditionally:
```ts
if (deleteOrphans) {
  await ctx.db.delete(summary._id);
} else {
  if (expectedCanonicalNames.has(canonicalName)) {
    await ctx.db.delete(summary._id);
  }
}
```

findings.description:
Lines 136-141 compute `latestAiVerdict` using a ternary:
```ts
const latestAiVerdict = summary.latestAiVerdict === 'avoid' ? 'avoid' :
  summary.latestAiVerdict === 'trial_next' ? 'trial_next' : summary.latestAiVerdict;
```
The else branch returns `summary.latestAiVerdict` unchanged. This is equivalent to just `summary.latestAiVerdict` — the conditional adds no logic and is misleading.
